Last month, Green Africa Foundation founder Isaac Kalua wrote an article on how Kenya can eradicate poverty. I wish to build on it as regards the role of education in the management of counties and, by extension, combating poverty.
Mr Kalua stated, among others, the fact that devolution has opened up an opportunity to every county to identify in the field of agriculture, marine and livestock development items that they have competitive advantages in over other counties and specialise in exploiting them. Examples include growing mangoes in Makueni and bananas in Kisii.



