Secondly, and most importantly, he raised the issue of taking county leaderships into account through measurable changes that can be attributed to them as they work towards raising the standard of living of residents.
Let us go to the basics. Way back in 2003, the Ministry of Planning released data on poverty indices in every location in Kenya except in the then-North Eastern Province.



