I also attended the Royal Agricultural Show in Birmingham. One entrepreneur was exhibiting the use of aloe vera jelly to treat burns in livestock to full recovery, let alone a myriad other cosmetic and medicinal uses. At an agricultural expo in Tel Aviv, I came across cactus as animal feed with its fruit processed as jam for human consumption.
Back home, an investor from South Africa at one time wanted to lease for 15 years the New KCC factory at Miritini, near Mombasa. The intention was to convert it to process soya paste instead of milk. The investor said that soya grown along the coast between Mozambique and Somalia was of high quality. Given the chance, he would have helped farmers in the coastal districts to plant soya with a ready market from huge military ships that often dock at Mombasa.
Amarula wine
In Eldoret, one investor purchases chili and exports it to Germany but the supply is insufficient. Likewise, there is potential, yet unexplored, for growing marula trees and harvesting the fruits for processing into amarula wine as is done in South Africa, Namibia and Angola. The tree grows in the wild in the counties of Baringo, Samburu, Elgeyo Marakwet, Machakos, Makueni and West Pokot.



